# Blog Assets Directory

Place your blog post images in this folder.

## Recommended Image Specifications:

### Blog Cards / Related Stories:
- **Aspect Ratio:** 16:9
- **Recommended Size:** 750px × 422px
- **Format:** JPG or PNG
- **File Size:** < 200KB (optimized)

### Featured Blog Hero:
- **Aspect Ratio:** 16:9
- **Recommended Size:** 1200px × 675px
- **Format:** JPG or PNG
- **File Size:** < 300KB (optimized)

### Hero Image (Detail Page):
- **Aspect Ratio:** 16:9
- **Recommended Size:** 1200px × 675px
- **Format:** JPG or PNG
- **File Size:** < 300KB (optimized)

## Naming Convention:

Use descriptive, URL-friendly names:
- `universal-editor-hero.png`
- `content-fragments-thumb.png`
- `headless-forms-card.jpg`

## Where to Get Images:

1. **Unsplash** (free): https://unsplash.com/
2. **Pexels** (free): https://www.pexels.com/
3. **Adobe Stock** (licensed): https://stock.adobe.com/
4. **Custom screenshots** from your AEM Forms interface
5. **Design team** created graphics

## Example File Structure:

```
assets/
└── blog/
    ├── universal-editor-hero.png
    ├── universal-editor-thumb.png
    ├── content-fragments.png
    ├── headless-forms.png
    ├── form-analytics.png
    ├── accessibility.png
    ├── performance.png
    ├── integration.png
    └── multi-step.png
```

## After Adding Images:

1. Commit to git: `git add assets/ && git commit -m "Add blog images"`
2. Push: `git push`
3. Images will be available at: `https://main--aem-forms-blogs--singhkh.aem.page/assets/blog/yourimage.png`

